<plot>This is a brief travelogue that begins with a look at the delicate art of flower arranging; the voice-over narration explains some of its art and symbolism as we watch a kneeling woman completing one. Then it's on to the deer park near the Todaiji Buddhist Temple in Nara. It concludes with views of Mount Fuji, including a romantic walk in its shadow.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?415599</url></doc>
